As Albino processed his options in the blink of an eye, he realized that his usual tactics were of little use against the formidable android standing before him. Bullets, which usually marked the opening of his fights, would bounce harmlessly off its thick metal exterior, and his expertise in martial arts and pressure points would be futile against a foe devoid of flesh and bone. Even his extrasensory abilities, honed through years of training, did not seem to fit this mechanical adversary.
